{{infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Atlas of the British Flora | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:AtlasOfTheBritishFlora.jpg | caption = First edition | author = [[Franklyn Perring]] and [[Max Walters|S. Max Walters]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom | language = English | series = | genre = | publisher = [[Botanical Society of the British Isles]] | release_date = 1962 | media_type = Print | pages = | isbn = 0-901158-19-4 | isbn_note = (3rd edition) | oclc= 28734311 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
The '''''Atlas of the British Flora''''' is a book by [[Franklyn Perring]] and [[Max Walters|S. Max Walters]], published by the [[Botanical Society of the British Isles]].
It was first published in 1962, with a second edition published in 1976, and a third in 1982.
The atlas contains [[10-km square distribution maps]] for all non-critical native and frequently occurring alien vascular plant species found in Britain and Ireland.
{{Clear}}
